article.description: Cameron Krutwig matched his career high with 24 points as Loyola of Chicago beat Saint Joseph's 85-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago over St. Joseph's 85-68
article.linkText: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago over St. Joseph's 85-68
article.story: CHICAGO -- Cameron Krutwig matched his career high with 24 points as Loyola of Chicago beat Saint Joseph's 85-68 on Saturday. Marquise Kennedy had 16 points and five rebounds for Loyola of Chicago (2-2). Tate Hall added 16 points and seven rebounds. Aher Uguak had 12 points and five assists for the hosts. Taylor Funk had 15 points for the Hawks (2-2). Ryan Daly added 13 points, 10 rebounds and six assists. Chereef Knox had 12 points. He also had eight turnovers. Loyola of Chicago plays IUPUI at home on Wednesday. Saint Joseph's takes on Florida on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
